# 62071738f517457ab608683bdab3c57b
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSMimeHdrFieldRemove.en.rst:34
msgid ""
"Removes the MIME field located at :arg:`field` within :arg:`bufp` from "
"the header located at :arg:`hdr` within :arg:`bufp`."
msgstr ""

# 97afe24559bd46258d3fa6fe13b66e4e
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSMimeHdrFieldRemove.en.rst:37
msgid ""
"If the specified field cannot be found in the list of fields associated "
"with the header then nothing is done."
msgstr ""

# 625b1be4037646508ad7c3c9cd011e62
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSMimeHdrFieldRemove.en.rst:42
msgid ""
"Removing the field does not destroy the field. It only detaches the "
"field, hiding it from the printed output. The field can be reattached "
"with a call to :c:func:`TSMimeHdrFieldAppend`.  If you do not use the "
"detached field you should destroy it with a call to "
":c:func:`TSMimeHdrFieldDestroy` and release the handle field with a call "
"to :c:func:`TSHandleMLocRelease`."
msgstr ""

